48:17.705 --> 48:23.615
[SPEAKER_06]: When all the Prime Minister can say to her is that what the position is in Wales, Janet, I don't know.

48:23.635 --> 48:25.458
[SPEAKER_06]: You may not be interested in the position in Wales.

48:25.478 --> 48:31.788
[SPEAKER_06]: You may be interested in the position that you're facing and want a Prime Minister who takes responsibility for what he is responsible for.

48:32.048 --> 48:38.899
[SPEAKER_06]: But what you'll get with the Prime Minister is somebody who makes a promise saying, I will be held personally responsible for bringing those waiting lists down.

48:38.919 --> 48:40.081
[SPEAKER_06]: At the moment, they don't come down.

48:40.101 --> 48:40.542
[SPEAKER_06]: What does he do?

48:40.562 --> 48:41.824
[SPEAKER_06]: He blames everybody else.

48:41.844 --> 48:42.345
[SPEAKER_06]: OK, Keir Starmer.

48:42.325 --> 48:44.567
[SPEAKER_06]: It's a personal responsibility, actually.

48:44.587 --> 48:52.275
[SPEAKER_16]: Actually, sorry, can I just intervene there and ask very specifically then, Keir Starmer, what would you do about the doctor strikes that Rishi Sunak raised?

48:52.295 --> 48:55.158
[SPEAKER_16]: Can you answer that very directly to Rishi Sunak?

48:55.178 --> 48:56.119
[SPEAKER_06]: We've got to resolve them.

48:56.379 --> 49:00.203
[SPEAKER_06]: And for months and months and months, the Prime Minister hasn't resolved them.

49:00.223 --> 49:02.144
[SPEAKER_06]: They've been arguing about who gets in the room.

49:02.465 --> 49:06.349
[SPEAKER_06]: You've got to get in the room, you've got to resolve it, because the NHS needs to get back to work.

49:06.529 --> 49:08.791
[SPEAKER_06]: But we've also got to bring down the waiting list.

49:08.811 --> 49:09.852
[SPEAKER_06]: We've got a plan.

49:09.832 --> 49:13.481
[SPEAKER_06]: for 40,000 extra appointments each and every week.

49:13.501 --> 49:16.388
[SPEAKER_06]: That's 2 million a year to bring those waiting lists down.

49:16.408 --> 49:17.731
[SPEAKER_06]: They're at a record high.

49:18.012 --> 49:24.086
[SPEAKER_06]: And under the last Labour government, the record was waiting lists right down, satisfaction in NHS at a record high.

49:24.106 --> 49:26.492
[SPEAKER_06]: That's completely been turned on its head.

49:26.552 --> 49:27.655
[SPEAKER_06]: OK, Rishi Sunak.

49:28.867 --> 49:53.102
[SPEAKER_07]: I'm really grateful for everyone in the NHS for working so hard and we have now settled pay rises with everyone in the NHS except for the junior doctors and of course I want to do that to make sure it's fair and affordable though but despite being offered the most generous pay settlement anywhere in the NHS and indeed the public sector the Union are demanding a 35% pay rise and I don't want to raise your taxes to pay for that because I don't think it's right but I will say this

49:55.934 --> 50:01.964
[SPEAKER_07]: So when Keir Starmer says he'll resolve it, he hasn't explained to you how, but I will say this... OK, perhaps you can answer that, Keir Starmer.

50:02.305 --> 50:03.727
[SPEAKER_06]: Well, we wouldn't pay the 35%.

50:04.048 --> 50:05.710
[SPEAKER_06]: We've already said that to the doctors.

50:05.750 --> 50:11.159
