52:27.691 --> 52:30.440
[SPEAKER_16]: told me there was a plan ready to go on this.

52:30.882 --> 52:31.825
[SPEAKER_16]: We're still waiting.

52:32.367 --> 52:37.765
[SPEAKER_16]: Will you both now commit to a fully funded solution in your manifesto this time round?

52:38.287 --> 52:38.889
[SPEAKER_16]: Yes or no?

52:39.009 --> 52:39.912
[SPEAKER_16]: Rishi Sunak.

52:40.077 --> 52:42.741
[SPEAKER_07]: Yes, well, we've already implemented charging reform.

52:42.881 --> 52:44.964
[SPEAKER_07]: Pilots are in place to implement the reforms.

52:45.264 --> 52:46.986
[SPEAKER_07]: They will be rolled out later this year.

52:47.287 --> 52:50.010
[SPEAKER_16]: It will be fully funded in your manifesto.

52:50.030 --> 52:53.895
[SPEAKER_07]: We've already given social care an extra $8 billion because the pressures are immediate.

52:53.915 --> 52:56.279
[SPEAKER_07]: And the pilot reforms are there for charging.

52:56.299 --> 52:57.741
[SPEAKER_16]: OK, we heard that answer.

52:58.101 --> 52:58.862
[SPEAKER_16]: Yes or no?

52:58.842 --> 53:04.529
[SPEAKER_06]: We will have a plan for social care, and like everything else in our manifesto, it will be fully costed and fully funded.

53:04.850 --> 53:15.343
[SPEAKER_06]: It starts with the workforce, because as you know, one of the biggest problems in social care is that the workforce is fragmented, poor conditions, and many, many people.

53:15.363 --> 53:15.743
[SPEAKER_06]: Thank you.

53:15.843 --> 53:17.325
[SPEAKER_06]: You talk about the workforce.

53:17.586 --> 53:18.707
[SPEAKER_06]: If I could just pick up on this workforce.

53:18.687 --> 53:24.394
[SPEAKER_07]: because it is important, because there's no way to get Janet and everyone else the care they need without a workforce.

53:24.414 --> 53:24.534
[SPEAKER_07]: OK.

53:24.554 --> 53:26.576
[SPEAKER_07]: But the British Medical Association... All right, thank you.

53:26.596 --> 53:31.081
[SPEAKER_07]: ..has warned that Keir Starmer's pension tax... OK. ..risks an exodus of doctors.

53:31.141 --> 53:32.563
[SPEAKER_07]: We're talking about doctors from the NHS.

53:32.583 --> 53:34.525
[SPEAKER_07]: OK, we are going to... Gentlemen, please.

53:34.545 --> 53:35.086
[SPEAKER_07]: Gentlemen, actually...

53:35.106 --> 53:35.987
[SPEAKER_07]: It's all joined up.

53:36.147 --> 53:37.669
[SPEAKER_16]: But it's all joined up, but this is an important point.

53:37.689 --> 53:39.371
[SPEAKER_16]: Thank you very much indeed.

53:39.411 --> 53:41.614
[SPEAKER_16]: We're going to come on to tax very shortly.

53:41.634 --> 53:42.194
[SPEAKER_03]: But this is about the NHS.

53:42.214 --> 53:43.276
[SPEAKER_16]: I am going to say...

53:43.296 --> 53:43.716
[SPEAKER_16]: Yes.

53:43.696 --> 53:46.759
[SPEAKER_16]: Tax will run through a lot of what we're discussing this evening.

53:46.779 --> 53:48.722
[SPEAKER_16]: We will return very specifically to it.

53:49.022 --> 53:54.929
[SPEAKER_16]: And I just want to stay on the issue of public services and take a quick fire on education.

53:55.690 --> 53:56.030
[SPEAKER_16]: OK?

53:56.230 --> 54:03.699
[SPEAKER_16]: We've had Harry, a message from Harry, who's a teacher just starting out, and Deborah, who has been a primary school head for 40 years.

54:04.079 --> 54:07.543
[SPEAKER_16]: They've both been in touch with us to tell us effectively the same thing.

54:07.523 --> 54:11.799
[SPEAKER_16]: that they cannot believe how bad things are in their sector.

54:12.101 --> 54:14.550
[SPEAKER_16]: They want to know what you can do for them.

54:14.570 --> 54:16.116
[SPEAKER_16]: Rishi Sunak.

54:16.467 --> 54:20.753
[SPEAKER_07]: Yes, well, I think education is the most powerful way that you can transform people's lives.

54:20.773 --> 54:41.040
[SPEAKER_07]: That was something that my parents raised me with, and I'm grateful to all our teachers for what they're doing, which is why we're backing our schools with record investment at the moment, but also reforming how we teach our kids, which is why I'm proud that, right now, English schoolchildren are the best readers anywhere in the Western world, and that is testament to the hard work of teachers and the reforms of this Conservative government.

54:41.020 --> 54:42.442
[SPEAKER_06]: Well, there's a pattern here, isn't there?

54:42.462 --> 54:44.926
[SPEAKER_06]: We've just been talking about the NHS, and Janet says it's broken.

54:45.166 --> 54:48.651
[SPEAKER_06]: We've now gone to education, and the teachers say that's broken as well.

54:48.851 --> 54:54.880
[SPEAKER_06]: And I know the Prime Minister has already said in the first however many minutes of this debate that he doesn't want to have anything to do with the last 14 years.

54:55.080 --> 54:58.925
[SPEAKER_06]: I'm sorry, Prime Minister, you may want to just cast it off, but everybody else is living with it.

54:59.206 --> 55:06.797
[SPEAKER_06]: When it comes to schools, we desperately need more teachers, because in secondary schools, we do not have the teachers we need.

55:07.077 --> 55:09.981
[SPEAKER_06]: So, for example, on key issues like maths,

55:09.961 --> 55:16.772
[SPEAKER_06]: We have maths being taught, and parents watching this will know, by supply teachers, by PE teachers, but not maths teachers.

55:17.113 --> 55:30.315
[SPEAKER_06]: So we would have in place, one of our first steps would be to recruit 6,500 teachers to fill those gaps, which will help the existing teachers who are struggling to cope with the mess that this government has left them in.

55:30.295 --> 55:37.676
[SPEAKER_16]: So tell Rishi Sunak why you're going to raise VAT on private schools to achieve the money that you say you will spend on those extra teachers.

55:37.736 --> 55:38.739
[SPEAKER_16]: Why are you making that choice?

55:38.759 --> 55:39.320
[SPEAKER_16]: Tell Rishi Sunak.

55:39.340 --> 55:45.317
[SPEAKER_06]: Because I believe every child should have the teachers they need in the core subjects like maths.

55:45.297 --> 55:52.328
[SPEAKER_06]: I think, for a child in a state secondary school who doesn't have a core teacher in something like maths, is going to live with that for the rest of their lives.

55:52.368 --> 55:54.832
[SPEAKER_06]: It's not a one-year problem or a two-year problem.

55:55.032 --> 55:57.556
[SPEAKER_06]: If they're in their GCSEs, it's for life.

55:57.576 --> 55:59.779
[SPEAKER_06]: And, therefore, we will have 6,500 recruits.

55:59.980 --> 56:03.425
[SPEAKER_06]: OK. We will get rid of the tax break on private schools to pay for it.

56:03.445 --> 56:04.446
[SPEAKER_06]: That's a tough choice.

56:04.486 --> 56:06.049
[SPEAKER_06]: I do understand that.

56:06.069 --> 56:06.850
[SPEAKER_06]: It's a tough choice.

56:06.830 --> 56:12.399
[SPEAKER_06]: Rishi Sunak, you've explained the policy, thank you.

56:12.419 --> 56:14.563
