56:48.270 --> 56:54.779
[SPEAKER_06]: They put in pretend Labour policies to the Treasury, and then they get a false readout.

56:55.119 --> 57:00.767
[SPEAKER_06]: So I'll just tell you, what they've put in for this analysis is a mental health policy that isn't the Labour Party's policy.

57:00.947 --> 57:02.369
[SPEAKER_06]: He's put in one of his own policies.

57:02.690 --> 57:06.235
[SPEAKER_06]: He's asked the civil service to cost it, and they've come up with this figure of £2,000.

57:06.255 --> 57:06.755
[SPEAKER_06]: The expert...

57:07.056 --> 57:09.780
[SPEAKER_06]: They are an independent civil service.

57:09.840 --> 57:10.741
[SPEAKER_06]: All right, I think...

57:10.761 --> 57:11.502
[SPEAKER_06]: He's put it twice.

57:11.562 --> 57:12.223
[SPEAKER_06]: I do need to deal with it.

57:12.203 --> 57:17.649
[SPEAKER_16]: Gentlemen, please, may I just say that people are going to have a lot of figures to get their heads around tonight.

57:17.709 --> 57:29.582
[SPEAKER_16]: I'm not saying that people are more than capable of calculating that rapidly at home, but I do want to actually draw the focus then, given we're on this patch, very specifically onto the question of tax.

57:29.602 --> 57:35.249
[SPEAKER_16]: I want to talk very specifically about tax before we finish this first half of our debate.

57:35.689 --> 57:40.995
[SPEAKER_16]: Can we clarify the similarities in your positions?

57:40.975 --> 57:44.642
[SPEAKER_16]: Please raise your hand if I am wrong.

57:46.245 --> 57:49.552
[SPEAKER_16]: You, as Prime Minister, will not raise income tax.

57:51.335 --> 57:54.502
[SPEAKER_16]: You will not raise national insurance in the next Parliament.

57:55.784 --> 58:00.874
[SPEAKER_16]: And other than Labour on private schools, you will not raise VAT.

