58:47.368 --> 58:49.971
[SPEAKER_06]: So, we will raise those, but we won't raise the others.

58:49.991 --> 58:50.571
[SPEAKER_16]: Rishi Sunak.

58:50.952 --> 59:00.642
[SPEAKER_07]: Yes, well, we have already scrapped the Nondon regime and we have a £0.75 tax on energy companies, but independent Treasury civil servants have costed Labour's policies and it's £2,000.

59:00.682 --> 59:03.745
[SPEAKER_07]: But you asked for specifics, Julie, so let's have a specific difference.

59:03.845 --> 59:05.387
